    <string name="security_info_title">How IronVault Protects You</string>
    <string name="security_info_text">IronVault is completely offline-first. We do not use any analytics, trackers, or remote servers. All your passwords, usernames, and notes are encrypted on your device using military-grade AES-256-GCM encryption. The encryption key is derived locally using high-iteration PBKDF2. Your Master Password is the sole key, and it never leaves your device. If you use Google Drive backup, the uploaded file is fully encrypted with your Master Password, so even Google cannot read your vault.</string>

